      • build

        public static RestClient build(Object impl,
                               Marshall m)
        Convenience method for creating a Restclient over the specified REST implementation bean or bean class.

        Equivalent to calling:

        MockRestClient.create(impl, m).build();

        Parameters:
        impl - The REST bean or bean class annotated with @RestResource.
        If a class, it must have a no-arg constructor.
        m - The marshall to use for specifying the Accept and Content-Type headers.
        If null, headers will be reset.
        Returns:
        A new MockRest object.

      • build

        public static RestClient build(Object impl,
                               Serializer s,
                               Parser p)
        Convenience method for creating a Restclient over the specified REST implementation bean or bean class.

        Equivalent to calling:

        MockRestClient.create(impl, s, p).build();

        Parameters:
        impl - The REST bean or bean class annotated with @RestResource.
        If a class, it must have a no-arg constructor.
        s - The serializer to use for serializing HTTP bodies.
        Can be null (will remove the existing serializer).
        p - The parser to use for parsing HTTP bodies.
        Can be null (will remove the existing parser).
        Returns:
        A new MockRest object.
